1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the finite blocklength regime, which is a topic of interest in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless communication systems and their development, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the performance of different relaying protocols and their impact on the overall system, which is a topic of interest in systems and control. 
4. cs.COM (Computational Complexity) - The paper does not directly deal with computational complexity, but it involves analyzing the performance of different communication protocols, which can be computationally intensive. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not deal with multimedia directly, but it involves analyzing the performance of wireless communication systems, which can be used for multimedia applications.
